  ### Term details:                                                           
                                                                              
  **ID:** CL:9900001 (temporary NTR ID in idrange:81)                         
                                                                              
  **Label:** iron-recycling macrophage                                        
                                                                              
  **Definition:** A tissue-resident macrophage specialised in the phagocytosis
  of senescent erythrocytes and the recycling of iron from degraded           
  haemoglobin, with iron export mediated by ferroportin (SLC40A1) (Ferreira   
  and Gahl, 2017). Identified across multiple prenatal human organs during    
  fetal development, with highest enrichment in later gestation when immune   
  effector gene programmes are progressively upregulated (Suo et al., 2022).  
  In prenatal skin (7-17 post-conception weeks), this macrophage subset co-   
  localises with endothelial cells in neurovascular microenvironments and     
  specifically promotes endothelial cell chemotaxis and angiogenesis (Gopee et
  al., 2024). The closest postnatal counterparts are splenic red pulp         
  macrophages and Kupffer cells.                                              
                                                                              
